'''Berit Erbe''' (4 September 1923 – 13 May 2009) was a Danish-Norwegian actress and theatrical historian.
She was born in [[Oslo]] and died in [[Bergen]]. After her theatre education she worked at the [[Royal Danish Theatre]] in [[Copenhagen]]. She took a [[magister degree]] in theatre aesthetics and history in Copenhagen in 1959. She was hired as a lecturer at the [[University of Bergen]] in 1969, took the [[dr.philos.]] degree on a thesis about [[Bjørn Bjørnson]] in 1973, and served as a professor from 1975 to 1988.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Berit Erbe|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=|location=|url=http://www.snl.no/Berit_Erbe|language=Norwegian|accessdate=4 June 2014}}</ref>
==Selected filmography== * ''[[The Crime of Tove Andersen]]'' (1953)
