'''Levon Panos Dabağyan''' (11 November 1933; [[Aksaray, Istanbul|Aksaray]], [[Fatih]], [[İstanbul]], Turkey – 7 May 2017, Istanbul)<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/uc-hilalin-fikir-babasi-levon-panos-dabagyan-hayatini-kaybetti-40451452|title=Üç hilalin fikir babası Levon Panos Dabağyan hayatını kaybetti|last=|first=|date=8 May 2017|work=Hürriyet|access-date=9 May 2017|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=tr}}</ref> was a Turkish writer and researcher of Armenian descent. A member of [[Turkish Historical Society]], he claimed that [[Armenian Genocide denial|there was no genocide of Armenians]].<ref>{{cite web| url = http://hnn.us/roundup/entries/32126.html| title= Levon Panos Dabagian: "Turkish history has never had genocide against Armenians"| publisher = History News Network| date = 15 November 2006| accessdate = 1 April 2010}}</ref>
He was the candidate in Istanbul for the far-right [[Nationalist Movement Party]] (MHP) in the [[Turkish general election, 1969|1969 Turkish parliamentary elections]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mhp.org.tr/htmldocs/kadrolar/detay_ba_2613/baskanlik_divani/35.html|title=Milliyetçi Hareket Partisi|last=|first=|date=26 February 2013|publisher=[[Nationalist Movement Party]]|language=tr|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=9 May 2017}}</ref>
